In this article, President Trump discusses Eli Lilly's decision to cap the prices of insulin at $35 per month. He praises the move and states that other companies will also follow suit now that legislation has uncovered the high prices. The President also mentions the impact his administration has had on hotel costs and air travel, with major carriers allowing children to fly for free. He believes that once these issues are exposed, it becomes difficult to defend them. When asked about student loans, Trump expresses confidence in being on the right side of the law but is unsure of the outcome in the Supreme Court.